titles.full: Even God Doesn't Know What to Make of You

summaries.short: Lucas and Job revisit their past and ponder the future; Proctor pays for Rebecca's recklessness.
summaries.full: Lucas recalls the history of his friendship with Job, while pondering the future--if there indeed will be one. Proctor and Emily pay the price for Rebecca's recklessness; Carrie and Gordon pick up the pieces of their shattered relationship; Stowe and Leo land a big fish; Bunker reconnects with his skinhead past; Deva gets a lesson about crime and punishment.

summaries.short: (Season Three Finale) Lucas and Gordon steel themselves for a bloody faceoff, as do Proctor and Rebecca.
summaries.full: (Season Three Finale) As Lucas recalls a secret chapter in his life, Job gets special treatment from a fan. Unexpectedly joined by Gordon, Lucas prepares to return to Genoa for a final negotiation with Stowe, or die trying. Proctor heads to Philly to settle a score. After a bloody denouement in Banshee, Brock finally gets what he's been wishing for.

titles.short: All the Wisdom I Got Left
titles.full: All the Wisdom I Got Left

summaries.short: Lucas and Brock head to Louisiana, and the infamous Underground fight club, in search of Chayton.
summaries.full: Lucas and Brock head to Louisiana, and the infamous Underground fight club, in search of Chayton. Stowe pieces together details about the Camp Genoa heist, and who might be responsible. Burton's torment turns to resolve; Sugar looks to repay an old boxing debt; Rebecca's initiatives put Proctor and Emily in harm's way.

summaries.short: Season Four Premiere. Lucas becomes immersed in a new Banshee crisis involving a vicious serial murderer.
summaries.full: Season Four Premiere. Haunted by his inability to locate Job following his abduction, Lucas returns to Banshee to find the town dramatically changed--with a new sheriff, a new mayor, and a serial murderer on the loose. Carrie, still guilt-ridden over the death of her husband Gordon, undergoes court-sanctioned therapy and looks to distract herself in familiar, violent, ways.

titles.full: You Can't Hide From the Dead

summaries.short: Distracted by his pursuit of Chayton, Lucas forges ahead with his audacious plan to rob Camp Genoa.
summaries.full: Despite Job's reservations, Lucas and his team pull off a daring heist at Camp Genoa. Lucas and Chayton are haunted by their recent deadly encounter. Calling a truce, Gordon and Carrie attempt an unusual intervention with Deva. Unbeknownst to her uncle, Rebecca heads to Philly to work out a deal with a spurned Proctor client.

summaries.short: Carrie embarks on a vigilante crusade; Brock eyes Lucas in the serial-murder case.
summaries.full: With her hunt for Job yielding no leads, Carrie vents her frustration by embarking on a vigilante crusade. A hillbilly meth dealer tempts fate by bringing his product into Banshee. Proctor reprimands Calvin for profiting from a seedy side business, and looks to expand his drug trade by partnering with a Colombian kingpin. Brock eyes Lucas in the serial-murder case.

titles.full: We Were All Someone Else Yesterday

summaries.short: A revenge-minded Lucas takes matters into his own hands; Rebecca endures a rebuke from Proctor.
summaries.full: Reduced to the status of 'observer' as the FBI plans a raid on the Redbone wilderness compound, Lucas decides to take matters into his own hands in his pursuit of Chayton. Still stung by Proctor's rebuke over her initiative in dealing with the Black Beards, Rebecca is further chagrined to learn of her uncle's burgeoning romance with Emily. Deva is drawn to a handsome stranger.
